Description:
GARAGING GALORE
This one owner 1970's solid 3 bed, 1 bath 8 car garage set on a 620 m2 block is just a stone throw from Northern Bay college and less than 5 mins from local Corio shopping village.
Suiting a young family starting out, a tradie lover with huge secure garaging for all your toys or a savvy investor with a potential rent of $340pw
This well loved and very neatly presented home comprises of solid hardwood floors throughout, a front formal inviting living room equipped with Rinnai gas heater and reverse cycle split and ceiling fan for all year-round comfort.
There is a fantastic private dining space easily accommodating 6+ and is positioned perfectly next to the updated kitchen, which comes with ample overhead cupboards, 6 burner gas cooking and L shaped breakfast bar seating up to 4.
Down the hall you will find 3 spacious bedrooms all with BIR, solid hardwood flooring and Master with two-way access and great natural light. There is also a split system AC servicing the bedroom areas.
The central bathroom and laundry area are well designed with two-way toilet door, corner shower and sunken bath for all your family's needs.
Outside is what sets this property apart from the rest is the HUGE secure pergola/garage area easily accommodating up to 8 cars with a Clearance of 2.4mt at the lowest point.
There is also a lockable garden shed and SLUG / workshop plus a low maintained rear yard ideal for children or your four-legged friend.
This neat as a pin property is ideally located walking distance to Northern Bay college, short drive to Corio shopping village and 5 km to Melbourne fwy access.

620m2 block

Description:
Flowing Floorplan... Family Focused... Formidable..!
ON The Market
This property is nestled in a quiet pocket of Corio in a highly sought-after family focused location desirably located close to shops, schools, and Melbourne commuter connectivity. This single level beauty ticks all the boxes for your next family home. Superbly set on approximately 626m2 of land and delivering an abundance of space for the entire family.
This family friendly floorplan comfortably accommodates three bedrooms all with built-in-robes, a well-appointed bathroom with vanity, bath, shower and separate toilet. The light filled kitchen has been beautifully updated with a modern feel, plus ample cupboard space, gas cooktop and electric oven. Adjoining the kitchen is the open plan dining followed by the family living zone. Step outside to the undercover paved entertaining area that enables you to make the most of this zone all year round. This great entertainer is sure to impress!
If its garage space you are after then look no further!? This large 3-4 car space garage also includes workshop! A connecting large driveway with single carport and side gate access to the backyard creating ideal storage potential for a caravan, boat, trailer, or any other toys you may have. Outside also enjoys a vegetable patch, fernery and well established and thriving gardens.
Added highlights include, gas heating, split system cooling and heating, near new floorboards through living, kitchen & dining, 5000 litre water tank, near new colour bond roofing, solar panels servicing the electricity to the home with the current owners having not had an electricity invoice for the last four years this home saves you money!
Here's a fabulous opportunity for a motivated and savvy buyer to take advantage of a well-established property - perfect for families, Melbourne commuters, first home buyers or investors alike.
With this well-connected location, life will be a breeze - close access to the Ring Road, local schools, public transport and all the amenities you could want and need at your fingertips.
Roncon Real Estate Always ON!

Description:
Position Perfect!
With your own street frontage this is the one you want to call youre own, spacious, private and matched by its comfort and convenience. This perfect one bedroom gem is situated in one of Geelongs most progressive suburbs, there is no better time to get your foot in the market with the best amenities and public transport at your doorstep.
Offering plenty of charm, the home impresses with an extra large functional and flowing floor plan, ample storage space, open plan in design and further comforted with split system air-conditioning and ceiling fans. The kitchen has been fitted with quality appliances while the large bathroom and laundry offers ample room for singles or couples alike.
Additional features include a lock up garage offering plenty of room for a workshop or added storage as well as an enclosed courtyard big enough to have the little ones running around.
If its an investment your after you will be pleased with the steady growth this pocket continues to have with an expected return of $220pw - $240pw.
Walking distance to Corio Village shopping precinct, cafes, public transport and only moments away from the Geelong Ring Road and Surf Coast Beaches, this one cant last long!
Insights: 1/1 Clive Court, Corio VIC 3214 was last sold in 2020.

Description:
Perfect Home or Investment
Recently painted throughout, this delightful single level brick home is ideal for the first home buyer or astute investors alike. Featuring 3 generous bedrooms with built-in robes to 2 and serviced by a central family bathroom. The home boasts a light-filled lounge, kitchen/dining zone which leads you to the large undercover carport, which could easily by utilised as an entertainment area. Other features include gas wall heating and air conditioning to the main lounge/living area and 2.0kw solar power system. Carpet and linoleum flooring throughout and tiles in the bathroom, single lock-up garage with space for a workshop and undercover single carport.
Corner the market with this great home situated on a generous block of 540m2 (approx.) which gives buyers a home with plenty of room to move, a great backyard for the kids to play in and well maintained front and back gardens, complete with fruit trees.
This home represents outstanding value within close proximity to all Corios great amenities including local schools & parks, Corio Village Shopping Centre, Aldi, local shops and cafes, transport and sporting facilities just around a few corners.
Houses come and go but golden opportunities like this are ones that you need to grab with both hands. Call today!
Insights: 18 Sharland Road, Corio VIC 3214 was last sold in 2020 and 174 other 3 bedroom house in Corio have recently been sold.

Description:
Tidy Family Abode on Spacious 840sqm (approx.) Block
This much-loved family home is ready for new memories to be made that will last a lifetime for families of all sizes! Situated on an incredibly generous block of 840sqm (approx.) is this impeccably well-kept 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom, 2 living area abode.
Features throughout the home include:
Master bedroom complete with ensuite & walk-in robe.
Remaining bedrooms with built-in robes.
Gas central heating.
Split-system heating/cooling.
Tiles throughout.
Carpets in bedrooms & 1st living area.
4 gas burner cooktop & electric oven.
Study.
Downlights.
Ceiling fans in bedrooms & study.
Undercover alfresco area as you step out into the backyard.
Gas hot water system.
Double lock up garage & workshop.
Double carport.
16 solar panels.
Conveniently located within close proximity to a plethora of amenities to satisfy every member of the family such as the Geelong Ring Road (2-minute drive), Bell Post Hill Shopping Centre (2-minute drive), Waterworld Leisure Centre (3-minute drive), Corio Village (4-minute drive), multiple schools including Kardinia International College & Northern Bay College (within a 5-minute drive).
Insights: 6 Wattle Place, Corio VIC 3214 was last sold in 2020 and 174 other 3 bedroom house in Corio have recently been sold.
